    spareHowtoRows:[['1. Enter starting amount','How much do you have saved today? Enter 0 if starting from scratch.'],['2. Monthly savings','How much can you set aside each month? Even small amounts grow significantly over time.'],['3. Expected return','Stock market historically returns 7-10% per year. Savings accounts give 2-4%. Be realistic.'],['4. Number of years','The longer you save, the more powerful the compound effect. Try 10, 20 and 30 years to see the difference.'],['5. Read the chart','The blue bars show your actual deposits. The green bars show interest earned. When green exceeds blue, compound interest has doubled your money.']],
    studieHowtoTitle:'How to use the Student Loan Calculator', studieHowtoDesc:'Step-by-step guide to student loans',
    studieHowtoRows:[['1. Choose study duration','How long is your degree? 3 years = bachelor, 5 years = master. Longer studies = more debt.'],['2. Are you completing a degree?','Completing a degree converts 40% of your loan to a grant (25% for the degree + 15% for credits). Without a degree: only 15%.'],['3. Base support','The 2025–2026 rate is 15,169 kr/month. Update if the rate changes.'],['4. Extras','Tuition fees or over 30? Add extra loans under "Extras".'],['5. Interest rate','Lånekassen charges approx. 5% variable interest (2025). Try different rates to see the impact.'],['6. Read the results','See total debt, grant share, and actual repayment. The rate comparison shows how much interest matters. The repayment plan shows year-by-year progress.'],['7. Tax deduction','You get 22% back on interest costs — "actual cost" shows what you really pay after the tax deduction.']],
